---
import Default from '../../layouts/Default.astro';
---
<Default title="HIVE Product Lab · Harshith Kantamneni" description="HIVE: an autonomous product engineering lab." current="labs">

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-parallax-layer hero-parallax-layer-1" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="hero-parallax-layer hero-parallax-layer-2" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="container">
      <span class="index-number">Lab module · live</span>
      <h1 style="max-width: 16ch;">HIVE Product Lab</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        An autonomous product engineering lab. A Director and specialist agents
        running on commodity hardware, kept honest by CI-bound external verification,
        pre-registered streak falsifiers, and a three-tier persistent memory.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-meta">
        <span><strong>Status</strong> Live</span>
        <span><strong>Active since</strong> 2026</span>
        <span><strong>Type</strong> Product engineering</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section style="padding-top: 0;">
    <div class="grid-editorial">

      <article class="body">
        <h2>What this lab is</h2>
        <p>
          An autonomous product engineering lab. A single Claude Opus instance acts
          as Director, dispatching specialist sub-agents (chief architect, mobile
          engineer, code reviewer, evaluator, red team, knowledge manager, and more)
          to plan, execute, and verify engineering work over long horizons.
        </p>
        <p>
          It runs in a tmux loop on a single MacBook. One cycle per Claude session.
          State persists across cycles via a three-tier markdown memory.
        </p>

        <h2>Operating model</h2>
        <ul style="padding-left: var(--space-5); line-height: var(--lh-body);">
          <li><strong>Director.</strong> Picks PRIMARY and SECONDARY work each cycle, dispatches specialists, owns cycle outcome</li>
          <li><strong>Quartet.</strong> Chief architect, CPO, red team, and applied researcher reviewing META-altitude proposals (4 of 4 NON-REJECT gate)</li>
          <li><strong>Specialists.</strong> Mobile engineers, build engineers, code reviewer, evaluator, vm-testing-lead, and others</li>
          <li><strong>Knowledge Manager.</strong> Closeout discipline at every cycle close</li>
          <li><strong>Evaluator.</strong> Independent verdict on cycle PASS, PARTIAL, or FAIL (binding)</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Verification discipline</h2>
        <p>Three structural principles, ratified May 2026:</p>
        <ol style="padding-left: var(--space-5); line-height: var(--lh-body);">
          <li><strong>External verdict.</strong> At least one verdict per cycle from a system the lab cannot edit (currently GitHub Actions CI on a public commit)</li>
          <li><strong>Pre-registered falsifier.</strong> Every streak claim declares, at open, a concrete observation that would invalidate it (immutable)</li>
          <li><strong>Adversarial payoff.</strong> At least one actor whose payoff increases when others' claims are falsified (cross-family verifier mechanism in progress)</li>
        </ol>

        <h2>Selected case studies</h2>
        <ul style="padding-left: var(--space-5); line-height: var(--lh-body);">
          <li>
            <a href="/harshithkantamneni.github.io/reports/recursive-verification-surface-collapse">Recursive Verification-Surface Collapse</a>.
            Three iterations of the same failure across 100+ cycles.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <p style="margin-top: var(--space-7); color: var(--text-secondary);">
          For the current cycle, recent dispatches, and what is shipping this week,
          see <a href="/harshithkantamneni.github.io/now">Now</a>.
        </p>
      </article>

      <aside class="marginalia">
        <p><strong>Lab type</strong></p>
        <p>Product engineering</p>

        <p style="margin-top: var(--space-5);"><strong>Active since</strong></p>
        <p>2026</p>

        <p style="margin-top: var(--space-5);"><strong>Hardware</strong></p>
        <p>Single MacBook (M3 Pro, 18 GB)</p>

        <p style="margin-top: var(--space-5);"><strong>Stack</strong></p>
        <p>Rust, mobile FFI, cross-platform native</p>

        <p style="margin-top: var(--space-5);"><strong>Memory</strong></p>
        <p>Three-tier markdown (hot, wiki, log)</p>

        <p style="margin-top: var(--space-5);"><strong>External verification</strong></p>
        <p>GitHub Actions CI bound to cycle PASS verdict</p>

        <p style="margin-top: var(--space-5);"><strong>Framework</strong></p>
        <p><a href="https://github.com/Drogon4231/autonomous-lab-systems">autonomous-lab-systems</a></p>

        <p style="margin-top: var(--space-5);"><strong>Live status</strong></p>
        <p><a href="/harshithkantamneni.github.io/now">/now</a></p>
      </aside>

    </div>
  </section>

</Default>
